  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a global issue with varying legal approaches across different nations. Here's an overview of comparative legal approaches:\n\n1. United States\n- Comprehensive legal framework (Bank Secrecy Act, USA PATRIOT Act)\n- Strict reporting requirements\n- Aggressive prosecution\n- Emphasis on financial institution compliance\n\n2. European Union\n- Unified regulatory approach through Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Centralized reporting mechanisms\n- Stronger emphasis on preventive measures\n- Harmonized legal standards across member states\n\n3. United Kingdom\n- Advanced regulatory framework\n- Sophisticated financial intelligence unit\n- Strong international cooperation\n- Robust asset recovery mechanisms\n\n4. Switzerland\n- Historically more lenient approach\n- Strong banking secrecy laws\n- Increasingly strict compliance requirements\n- Enhanced international transparency\n\n5. China\n- Centralized regulatory control\n- Strict criminal penalties\n- Growing emphasis on financial transparency\n- Developing comprehensive legal framework\n\n6. Russia\n- Evolving legal landscape\n- Inconsistent enforcement\n- Complex regulatory environment\n- Limited international cooperation\n\nEach jurisdiction has unique characteristics, reflecting different legal traditions, economic structures, and political priorities in combating money laundering.",
